Charles Carl Roberts IV, a 32-year-old truck driver, tragically took his own life in an Amish schoolhouse after holding children, teachers, and assistants hostage.
The horrific incident in Pennsylvania resulted in the deaths of five, including the gunman.
Roberts, who had a wife and children, had a darkened mood in recent days, hinting at a childhood grudge.
Motivated by past trauma, he carried out a heinous act that shocked those who knew him.
The Amish community mourns the loss, finding solace in their faith during this tragic event.
